spec: as3331
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__, __ior__, __ixor__ dict-presence (in-place &=, |=, ^=) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__iand__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __iand__. In-place bitwise AND (__iand__, &=) is the augmented assignment variant of __and__. asyncio types define no __and__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __iand__ is equally absent. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization guards; obj &= n is not a defined Python operation for these types. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage an integer permit counter fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines; the counter is not exposed for &= operations. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; in-place bitwise AND is undefined for coroutine handles. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores with no bitwise data model of any kind."
    - "Key finding (__ior__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __ior__. In-place bitwise OR (__ior__, |=) is the augmented assignment variant of __or__. asyncio types define no __or__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __ior__ is equally absent. Note: Python 3.9 introduced the | operator for dict merging via __ior__ on the built-in dict type, but asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives, not dict-like types. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization primitives with no in-place bitwise-OR semantics. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; |= is not defined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; items are managed through put()/get() coroutine calls only."
    - "Key finding (__ixor__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __ixor__. In-place bitwise XOR (__ixor__, ^=) is the augmented assignment variant of __xor__. asyncio types define no __xor__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __ixor__ is equally absent. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization primitives with no bitwise or in-place XOR semantics of any kind. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; ^= is not defined for pending result objects. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue types do not define __ixor__; they manage items solely through put()/get() coroutine calls."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 669 (__iand__/__ior__/__ixor__) — fourteen consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __iand__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__iand__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __iand__.
# In-place bitwise AND (__iand__, &=) is the augmented assignment variant
#   of __and__. asyncio types define no __and__ (wave 661), so __iand__ is
#   equally absent.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   obj &= n is not a defined Python operation for these types.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects; the counter
#   is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines. The internal
#   integer state is not exposed for &= operations.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; in-place bitwise
#   AND is undefined for coroutine handles.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no
#   bitwise data model of any kind.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

